    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-22T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/16795: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Earle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-22T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 22, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>458. Legation’s 457, November 22.<note n="3" xml:id="d357fn3">Not printed.</note>
                    The Prime Minister’s speech, particularly his references to Bulgaria’s
                    prevention of the formation of a Balkan bloc, her fidelity to Germany and her
                    attitude towards communism, is interpreted here as being designed to make up for
                    Bulgaria’s failure to take positive action against Russia by emphasizing the
                    contributions her policy has made to the Axis cause. It is considered that
                    Hitler’s reference to Bulgaria in his speech of November 8 did not show complete
                    approval of Bulgaria’s attitude in the Russian conflict.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
